            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Neither of the two users in the usability study understood it, and they were both previous IntelliJ users. I don't really care what is standard for IntelliJ if that standard is incomprehensible. :-)\n\nWe should care about what is best for our users. If we're successful, our users will be using IntelliJ more for Flutter than for other languages.\n\nAlso, if what we do is a substantial improvement over what the standard is (which I think my proposal would be), then I would not be surprised if the rest of the IntelliJ ecosystem followed suit. Let's be leaders and aim higher than the mediocre status quo. Don't be happy with what came before if it sucks. :-)\n",
